# Vendored RADEv2 C subset

Source: `/home/rafael2k/files/rhizomatica/hermes/radae` @ `38e354f7a83cb1a9970630a00a479132d65f34d7`.

This directory carries the pure-C RADEv2 TX/RX subset needed for later in-process linkage inside `hermes-radio-daemon`:
- upstream RADEv2 encoder/decoder, RX/TX wrappers, DSP, and generated model blobs
- a pure-C-only `src/rade_api_pure_c.c` extracted from upstream `src/rade_api.c`
- a minimal `src/rade_nnet.c` runtime covering the float-weight DNN helpers used by the compiled 250725 model
- `sources.mk` and a standalone `Makefile` so later linkage can consume the vendored sources without shelling out to external binaries

Notes:
- use `rade_tx_v2_pure_c_open()` / `rade_rx_v2_pure_c_open()` from `src/rade_api.h`
- legacy Python-backed `rade_open()` is intentionally not vendored beyond a stub

Standalone sanity build:

```sh
make -C vendor/radev2
```
